<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C78DDF8422663F83C" bold="true" box="[136,313,1920,1942]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">FIGURE 6. A–D.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7915F84226BFF83F" box="[320,485,1920,1942]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7D164C7915F84226BBF83F" authorityName="Martius ex Colla" authorityYear="1833" box="[320,481,1920,1942]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nemorensis">Sida nemorensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C79BFF8422558F83C" bold="true" box="[490,514,1920,1941]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">A.</emphasis>
Flower. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7A02F8422537F83C" bold="true" box="[599,621,1920,1941]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">B.</emphasis>
Branch with leaves and flowers. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7BE4F8422493F83F" bold="true" box="[945,969,1920,1942]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">C.</emphasis>
Leaves and schizocarps. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7C95F842238DF83C" bold="true" box="[1216,1239,1920,1941]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">D.</emphasis>
Calyx and mericarps. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C78DDF86627ECF810" bold="true" box="[136,182,1956,1977]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">E–J.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C78EBF8662609F810" box="[190,339,1956,1977]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7D164C78EBF8662615F810" authorityName="Rodrigo" authorityYear="1937" box="[190,335,1956,1977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradoxa">Sida paradoxa</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C790FF866262AF810" bold="true" box="[346,368,1956,1977]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">E.</emphasis>
Flower. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C799DF8662680F810" bold="true" box="[456,474,1956,1977]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">F.</emphasis>
Branch with leaves and stipules. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7B73F8662465F813" bold="true" box="[806,831,1956,1978]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">G.</emphasis>
Abaxial surface of leaf. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7C61F8662317F810" bold="true" box="[1076,1101,1956,1977]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">H.</emphasis>
Habit. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7CC2F86623E4F810" bold="true" box="[1175,1214,1956,1977]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">I–J.</emphasis>
Schizocarps. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7D1DF8662223F810" bold="true" box="[1352,1401,1956,1977]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">K–P.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7DD4F86627A0F874" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7D164C7DD4F86627ACF874" authorityName="Cavanilles" authorityYear="1785" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="planicaulis">Sida planicaulis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7956F80A2646F874" bold="true" box="[259,284,1992,2013]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">K.</emphasis>
Flowers. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C79D7F80A26C3F874" bold="true" box="[386,409,1992,2013]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">L.</emphasis>
Adaxial surface of leaf. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7ACDF80A25EEF874" bold="true" box="[664,692,1992,2013]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">M.</emphasis>
Abaxial surface of leaf. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7BE0F80A2497F874" bold="true" box="[949,973,1992,2013]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">N.</emphasis>
Branch with distichous leaves arrangement. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7DC6F80A22F6F877" bold="true" box="[1427,1452,1992,2014]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">O.</emphasis>
Schizocarps. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7952F82E2643F7A8" bold="true" box="[263,281,2028,2049]" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">P.</emphasis>
Branch with flowers and schizocarps. Photographs A–B by Amaury Junior, C–P by Martin Grings (C–D from 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7D164C7D67F82E27A6F78C" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="118">Krapovickas &amp; Cristóbal</emphasis>
38480, HAS).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7E164F78E8FF5C279BFE39" blockId="14.[136,1452,158,653]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F78E8FF5C26D4FF11" bold="true" box="[189,398,158,184]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
—The species is distinguished from other species of section 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7C79FF5C2392FF11" box="[1068,1224,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Malacroideae</emphasis>
by its stems without roots; subentire margin of leaves, only with three apical teeth; staminal tube glabrous; petals 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7E164F7CDBFF002387FF74" box="[1166,1245,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7E164F7D77FF0027CFFEA8" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="13.[136,229,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. A–D. Sida nemorensis. A. Flower. B. Branch with leaves and flowers. C. Leaves and schizocarps. D. Calyx and mericarps. E–J. Sida paradoxa. E. Flower. F. Branch with leaves and stipules. G. Abaxial surface of leaf. H. Habit. I–J. Schizocarps. K–P. Sida planicaulis. K. Flowers. L. Adaxial surface of leaf. M. Abaxial surface of leaf. N. Branch with distichous leaves arrangement. O. Schizocarps. P. Branch with flowers and schizocarps. PhotographsA–B by Amaury Junior, C–P by Martin Grings (C–D from Krapovickas &amp; Cristóbal 38480, HAS)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415499/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Figures 6E– J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7E164F78F5FF242789FEA9" box="[160,211,230,256]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">14K</figureCitation>
; 
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B7E164F7888FF242677FEA9" box="[221,301,230,256]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7913FF242542FEA8" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[326,536,230,257]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="5 - 45" refId="ref19451" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2006) Las especies argentinas y de paises vecinos de Sida secc. Nelavaga (Malvaceae, Malveae). Bonplandia 15: 5 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 151 - 289" type="journal article" year="2006">Krapovickas 2006</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7E164F7A7CFF242596FEA9" authorityName="Rodrigo" authorityYear="1937" box="[553,716,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradoxa">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7A7CFF242596FEA9" box="[553,716,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida paradoxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the other species of Sect. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7D5AFF2422F1FEA9" box="[1295,1451,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Malacroideae</emphasis>
of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7E164F78FFFEC826D2FE8D" box="[170,392,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7E164F79C2FEC8256CFE8D" authorityName="A. Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1825" box="[407,566,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anomala">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F79C2FEC8256CFE8D" box="[407,566,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida anomala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the cuneate-truncate leaf blades, subentire, with three teeth at the apex; flowers 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7E164F78B1FEEC2668FEE0" box="[228,306,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" unit="cm" value="2.5">2.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter; fruits with 5 mericarps (vs. linear leaf blades, serrate in the upper half; flowers 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7E164F7D00FEEC22D7FEE0" box="[1365,1421,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
in diameter; fruits with 7–8 mericarps). In the present work, photos of the species in its habitat are presented for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7E164F78E8FE5824ADFDED" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7E164F78E8FE5824ADFDED" blockId="14.[136,1452,158,653]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F78E8FE5825A1FE1D" bold="true" box="[189,763,410,436]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7E164F7B42FE582498FE1D" authorityName="Rodrigo" authorityYear="1937" box="[791,962,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradoxa">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7B42FE582498FE1D" box="[791,962,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida paradoxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7E164F7C1EFE5823E0FE1D" box="[1099,1210,410,436]" name="Argentina" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(only in 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7E164F7D62FE5827B6FE70" country="Argentina" name="Corrientes" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Corrientes province</collectingRegion>
) and in 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7E164F791DFE7C26D5FE71" box="[328,399,446,472]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, only in state of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7E164F7A1FFE7C2446FE71" box="[586,796,446,472]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7B79FE7C24A7FE70" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[812,1021,446,473]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="292 - 333" refId="ref19401" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2005) Malvaceae. In: Bacigalupo, N. M. (Ed.) Flora Ilustrada de Entre-Rios. 6 (4 b). Colecc. Ci. Inst. Nac. Tecnol. Agropecu, pp. 292 - 333." type="book chapter" year="2005">Krapovickas 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7C5CFE7C23BDFE71" author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[1033,1255,446,472]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7C39FE7D23FFFE71" box="[1132,1189,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7CA7FE7C22D8FE71" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[1266,1410,446,472]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
), in Park grassland (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7E164F7968FE2026FBFE54" box="[317,417,482,509]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="12.[136,229,2030,2052]" captionTargetBox="[315,1294,482,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-118@12.[258,1329,425,2006]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution map of Sida glaziovii, S. paradoxa, S. linifolia, S. nemorensis, S. planicaulis, S. potentilloides and S. rubifolia in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415497/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Figure 5</figureCitation>
). With the available records, the species presents an EOO of 46,921.776 Km² and an AOO of 100 Km². The species is here considered Endangered (EN), criterion B2b(i, ii, iii)c(i, ii), due to the continuous reduction observed in its habitat and its area of occupancy (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7B74FDE824B1FDED" author="Mapbiomas" box="[801,1003,554,580]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" refId="ref19791" refString="Mapbiomas (2020) Available from: https: // mapbiomas. org / (accessed 24 November 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Mapbiomas 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
